Buffett Asked to Invest in Medical Facility in South Korea’s Daegu City

-- B y   J u n   Y a n g
-- 
2011-03-21T00:26:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/buffett-asked-to-invest-in-medical-facility-in-south-korea-s-daegu-city.html
Billionaire investor  Warren Buffett 
responded positively to a request to invest in a medical
facility in Daegu City, South Korea, Mayor Kim Bum Il said
today.  Buffett is in the city to attend a ground-breaking ceremony
for a new factory being built by TaeguTec Ltd., a company his  Berkshire Hathaway Inc. (BRK/A)  has invested in through its Israeli
toolmaking unit Iscar Metalworking Cos.  Kim wasn’t more specific on Buffett’s response than saying
it had been positive.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jun Yang in Seoul at 
 jyang180@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
